Mike McCarty <jmccarty@digi.lonestar.org> wrote:
>Well, I thought I was the only one who put "Without Prejudice UCC 1-207"
>on all his signatures.
>
>Nice to meet another.
>
>Has it made any real difference to you? I had one bank teller tell me
>that she could not accept my paycheck with a conditional endorsement
>on it. I told her to talk to her legal department. Only hassle yet
>(been doing it for 2 years).

And after her legal department stopped laughing, they probably told her
to ignore it, since it it totally meaningless in that context.  It has
as much legal significance there as any other meaningless thing drawn
with your signature (e.g., happy faces, swastikas, peace signs, proofs
of Fermat's Last Theorem, etc.).

--Tim Smith

